<bibRefCitation author="Rondani, C." box="[270,496,1554,1581]" pageId="247" pageNumber="248" refId="ref368401" refString="Rondani, C. (1857) Dipterologiae italicae prodromus. Vol: II. Species italicae ordinis dipterorum in genera characteribus definita, ordinatim collectae, methodo analitica distinctae, et novis vel minus cognitis descriptis. Pars prima. Oestridae: Syrphfidae [sic!]: Conopidae. A. Stocchi, Parmae [= Parma], 264 pp., 1 pl. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 8160" type="book" year="1857">Rondani (1857: 89)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName box="[625,817,1554,1580]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Eumerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="247" pageNumber="248" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicolor">
<emphasis box="[625,817,1554,1580]" italics="true" pageId="247" pageNumber="248">Eumerus bicolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from just the male sex, without specifying the exact 
<taxonomicName box="[199,285,1590,1616]" family="Number" pageId="247" pageNumber="26" rank="family">number</taxonomicName>
of specimens, but giving a single measurement of length, despite there being 
<specimenCount box="[1144,1314,1590,1616]" pageId="247" pageNumber="248" type="generic">four specimens</specimenCount>
in the type series found in this study. Rondani attributed the species name to L. Bellardi. Three females in the MRSN (Box 53) are not included in the type series because of their sex. 
<bibRefCitation author="Sommaggio, D." box="[861,1134,1662,1689]" pageId="247" pageNumber="248" pagination="121 - 158" refId="ref373723" refString="Sommaggio, D. (2007) Revision of Diptera Syrphidae in Bellardi's Collection, Turin. Bollettino del Museo Regionale di Scienze Naturali di Torino, 24 (1), 121 - 158." type="journal article" year="2007">Sommaggio (2007: 136)</bibRefCitation>
designated a 
<typeStatus box="[1287,1390,1662,1688]" pageId="247" pageNumber="248">lectotype</typeStatus>
(
<specimenCount box="[1405,1427,1662,1688]" pageId="247" pageNumber="248" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
) and 
<typeStatus box="[247,409,1698,1724]" pageId="247" pageNumber="248">paralectotypes</typeStatus>
(
<specimenCount box="[425,492,1698,1725]" pageId="247" pageNumber="248" type="male">3 ♂♂</specimenCount>
).
</paragraph>
